                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 19 (PTI): Officers of general-rank in the army will now either execute administrative duties only or lead troops in operational formations, according to a new promotion policy implemented by the force.          The new policy for major generals and lieutenant generals categorised them into either staff or command streams based on their merit.                   
	 Pune (PTI): A 20-year-old white tiger, the first in India to have had root canal surgery, has died at a zoo near Pune. The tiger was kept in a separate cage because of old age and had stopped eating for the last few days.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Nine students of Jawaharlal Nehru University who were allegedly involved in ragging were rusticated for two years on Wednesday.
                                                                                                                           
